    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mango-and-scotch-bonnet-chicken-thigh-coconut-lentils-and-naan-croutons/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mango-and-scotch-bonnet-chicken-thigh-coconut-lentils-and-naan-croutons/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>red lentils </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>curry powder</strong> with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garam masala </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and the <strong>rinsed lentils</strong> and give everything a good mix</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mango-and-scotch-bonnet-chicken-thigh-coconut-lentils-and-naan-croutons/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your creamed coconut (if required!)</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> creamed coconut</strong> and 700ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>to the dish and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, cover with a lid, then put the dish in the oven for 20-22 min or until the lentils are tender \u2013 these are your <strong>coconut lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mango-and-scotch-bonnet-chicken-thigh-coconut-lentils-and-naan-croutons/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>chicken</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> pepper</strong>, <strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining garam masala</strong></p><p>Drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mango-and-scotch-bonnet-chicken-thigh-coconut-lentils-and-naan-croutons/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mango-and-scotch-bonnet-chicken-thigh-coconut-lentils-and-naan-croutons/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After the initial 15 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven, top the chicken with your <strong>mango & scotch bonnet sauce </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), then add the <strong>chopped naan</strong> to the other side of the tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and return the tray to the oven for 8-10 min or until golden and crisp and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>mango & scotch bonnet chicken and naan croutons</strong></p><p>Once the lentils are ready, add your <strong>spinach</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then set aside, covered, for 8-10 min or until wilted \u2013 these are your <strong>coconut & spinach lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mango-and-scotch-bonnet-chicken-thigh-coconut-lentils-and-naan-croutons/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>mango & scotch bonnet chicken </strong>finely</p><p>Serve the <strong>coconut & spinach lentils </strong>and top with the <strong>sliced mango & scotch bonnet chicken</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>naan croutons</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
